.TH smi-jails-update "1" "October 2025" "SMI Toolset 0.100.0" "SMI Jail Command"
.SH NAME
smi-jails-update \- Update all configured FreeBSD jails
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B smi-jails-update
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
.B smi-jails-update
is a batch utility that iterates through all jail configurations found in the SMI \fBetc/jails\fR directory and performs an update on each using \fBsmi-jail-update\fR(1).
.PP
The script:
.IP 1.
Ensures it is running as root (re-executes with \fBsudo\fR if necessary).
.IP 2.
Loads each jail's configuration to determine its name and path.
.IP 3.
Calls \fBsmi-jail-update\fR for each identified jail.
.SH AUTHOR
.PP
Command written by Imre Tabur.
Documentation written by Junie.
.SH "REPORTING BUGS"
.PP
Report smi-jails-update bugs to \fIinfo@setmy.info\fR
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.PP
